---+++ Status of Science Advisory Group (Composition, Needs, Planning)

   * Current membership of SAG
   * Topics to focus on when we next meet with SAG
   * When to meet with SAG again? How to organize?

%BLUE% *minutes:*

Discussed the possibility of adding addition members to assure good coverage at face to face meetings with the SAG. Should plan to give the SAG an update on our reviews. Kent asked if we should be sending out some sort of newsletter to the SAG on a regular basis (maybe twice a year) that captured some key aspects of the OSG of interest to the SAG. It may be possible to leverage off of existing newsletters within the OSG. Paul noted that he had sent the Annual Report to the NSF to the SAG before and could do the same with this year&#39;s report. In general, we felt that some means of maintaining a channel of communications with the SAG outside of face-to-face meetings would be useful.

Noted that having face to face meetings with the SAG at locations that showcase our stakeholders and their science missions could be very engaging to our SAG members.

Plan to discuss this further at the Face to Face Council meeting.

